This paper focuses on the interaction between modern applications and main memory, specifically DRAM chips. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.AR (Architecture), which deals with the design and analysis of computer systems. Additionally, the paper involves experimental studies and analysis of performance metrics, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.PF (Performance) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the need for memory optimizations in both hardware and software, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
